<h2 id="selected-text-formatting-options">Selected text formatting options</h2>
<p>Below are selected formatting options that may be useful in  in RC worskhop sites.</p>

<p><strong>Notes</strong></p>

<p>Use this syntaxâ€¦</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Wash your hands frequently
{: .note}
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>â€¦ to include a note that will look like this on the workshop website:</p>

<p class="note">Wash your hands frequently</p>

<p><strong>Warning</strong></p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Don't step on the snails!
{: .warn}
</code></pre></div></div>
<p class="warn">Donâ€™t step on the snails!</p>

<p><strong>Danger</strong></p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Snails armed and dangerous
{: .danger}
</code></pre></div></div>
<p class="danger">Snails armed and dangerous</p>

<p><strong>Prerequisites.</strong></p>

<p>This synaxâ€¦</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>- Basic slug identification
- Comfortable in the woods
{: .prereq}
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>â€¦will look like this:</p>

<p>Something else here</p>
<ul class="prereq">
  <li>Basic slug identification</li>
  <li>Comfortable in the woods</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Terminal input.</strong></p>

<p>Use this formatting to indicate that the participant should input text into the terminal or command line. Thisâ€¦</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Input
{: .label .label-green }
```
$ git status
```
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>â€¦ will appear like this in the workshop website:</p>

<p class="label label-green">Input</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ git status
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><strong>Terminal output.</strong></p>

<p>Shows the output resulting from an action.  This syntaxâ€¦</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Output
{: .label .label-yellow }
```
On branch master
Your branch is up-to-date with 'origin/master'.
nothing to commit, working tree clean
```
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>â€¦looks like this on the site:</p>

<p class="label label-yellow">Output</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>On branch master
Your branch is up-to-date with 'origin/master'.
nothing to commit, working tree clean
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><strong>Dropdowns</strong></p>

<p>You can use dropdowns to hide answers to questions. For example:</p>

<details>
<summary>Who was the first U.S. president?</summary>
<br />
George Washington.
</details>

<p>To create hidden content in a dropdown use this:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;details&gt;
&lt;summary&gt;This is the dropdown title&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
This is the hidden dropdown content.
&lt;/details&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>If you want it open by default:</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;details open&gt;
&lt;summary&gt;This is the dropdown title&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
This is the dropdown content that you can hide if you want to.
&lt;/details&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>
